 THE VALUE OF PHILOSOPHY IS, IN FACT, TO BE SOUGHT LARGELY IN ITS
 VERY UNCERTAINTY.  THE MAN WHO HAS NO TINCTURE OF PHILOSOPHY GOES
 THROUGH LIFE IMPRISONED IN THE PREJUDICES DERIVED FROM COMMON SENSE,
